--- OLLAMA ERROR ANALYSIS (attempt 1) ---
## Root Cause Analysis

The build fails at `%prep` because the source tarball `oterm-0.13.0.tar.gz` extracts to a directory named **`oterm_0.13.0`** (with underscores), but the spec file's `%setup -q` / `%autosetup` expects it as **`oterm-0.13.0`** (with hyphens):

```
+ cd oterm_0.13.0
/var/tmp/rpm-tmp.2mCQ3O: line 39: cd: oterm_0.13.0: No such file or directory
error: Bad exit status from /var/tmp/rpm-tmp.2mCQ3O (%prep)
```

## Fix

Add the `-n` flag to `%setup -q` (or `%autosetup`) in the `%prep` section with the actual extracted directory name (`oterm_0.13.0`).

If you need me to verify the exact tarball contents, run inside the build environment:
```bash
tar -tzf ~/rpmbuild/SOURCES/oterm-0.13.0.tar.gz | sed 's|/.*||' | sort -u
```

## Spec File Change

In the `%prep` section of `oterm.spec`:

```spec
%setup -q -n oterm_0.13.0
```

Or if using `%autosetup`:

```spec
%autosetup -n oterm_0.13.0
```
