--- OLLAMA ERROR ANALYSIS (attempt 2) ---
## Analysis

**Root Cause:** The RPM build fails because the executable `/usr/bin/oterm` (defined as an entry point in `pyproject.toml`) is installed during `%pyproject_install`, but it is not listed in any `%files` section of the spec file. RPM reports this as "Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found".

**Fix:** Add the binary to the `%files` section using `%{_bindir}/oterm`. Since `oterm` is a console application, you may also want to use `%defattr(-,root,root,-)` at the start of `%files` if not already present.

No additional `BuildRequires` are needed — all Python build dependencies (pip, setuptools, wheel) are provided by `%pyproject_wheel`. The missing piece is purely in the `%files` section.

```
%files
%defattr(-,root,root,-)
%{_bindir}/oterm
%{python_sitelib}/*
```
